    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7134" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πάλλω</span></b> , aor. 1 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πῆλε</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πῆλαι</span>, mid. aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πάλτο</span>,
          pass. pres. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πάλλεται</span>, part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">παλλόμενος</span>: act. <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">brandish, swing,
            shake</span> lots (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κλήρους</span>), <i><span class="en">Il. 3.316</span></i>, 324, and without <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κλήρους, Η 181</span>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            23.353</span></i>; mid., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">brandish</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">hurl</span>
          for oneself, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">cast lot</span> for oneself (or, of several,
          among one another), <i><span class="en">Il. 15.191</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 24.400</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἐν ἀσπίδος ἄντυγι πάλτο</span>, ‘struck,’
          ‘stumbled’ against the rim, <i><span class="en">Il.
            15.645</span></i>; fig., of the heart, ‘throb,’ ‘palpitate,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 22.452</span></i>, 461.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
